# SEASONALITY

# which one should we choose? ----
AIC(linear.fit)    
## [1] 3050.871
AIC(quadratic.fit)
## [1] 3052.395
AIC(cubic.fit) # cubic has lower AIC
## [1] 3029.163
# Calculate residuals after removing trend
data.notrend <- residuals(cubic.fit)

# Plot of residuals after removing trend
plot(data.notrend,
     main = "Residuals after removing trend",
     ylab = "Residuals",
     xlab = "Time",
     type = 'l',
     lwd = 2,
     lty = 1)

# Calculate the number of years in the data
years <- length(data) / 12

# Define manually indexes of months
jan <- seq(from = 1,  by = 12, length.out = years)
feb <- seq(from = 2,  by = 12, length.out = years)
mar <- seq(from = 3,  by = 12, length.out = years)
apr <- seq(from = 4,  by = 12, length.out = years)
may <- seq(from = 5,  by = 12, length.out = years)
jun <- seq(from = 6,  by = 12, length.out = years)
jul <- seq(from = 7,  by = 12, length.out = years)
aug <- seq(from = 8,  by = 12, length.out = years)
sep <- seq(from = 9,  by = 12, length.out = years)
oct <- seq(from = 10, by = 12, length.out = years)
nov <- seq(from = 11, by = 12, length.out = years)
dec <- seq(from = 12, by = 12, length.out = years)

# Create an empty vector to store means
means <- numeric(12)

# Evaluate mean for each month
means[1] <- mean(data.notrend[jan])
means[2] <- mean(data.notrend[feb])
means[3] <- mean(data.notrend[mar])
means[4] <- mean(data.notrend[apr])
means[5] <- mean(data.notrend[may])
means[6] <- mean(data.notrend[jun])
means[7] <- mean(data.notrend[jul])
means[8] <- mean(data.notrend[aug])
means[9] <- mean(data.notrend[sep])
means[10] <- mean(data.notrend[oct])
means[11] <- mean(data.notrend[nov])
means[12] <- mean(data.notrend[dec])

# Print means
print(means)
##  [1] -0.3145126 -5.0735460 -5.0597204 -4.5791108 -6.2711254 -6.9115363
##  [7] -4.4033880 -5.4921495 -3.5899564  2.3940862 15.9326910 23.3682681
# Using tapply() and cycle() function to calculate means more quickly
seas_means <- tapply(data.notrend, cycle(data), mean)

# Convert months to a factor
months <- as.factor(cycle(data))

# Fit linear model to estimate seasonal means
seas_model <- lm(data.notrend ~ months)

# Print coefficients of the model
print(coefficients(seas_model))
## (Intercept)     months2     months3     months4     months5     months6 
##  -0.3145126  -4.7590334  -4.7452078  -4.2645982  -5.9566128  -6.5970237 
##     months7     months8     months9    months10    months11    months12 
##  -4.0888754  -5.1776370  -3.2754438   2.7085987  16.2472036  23.6827807
# Remove intercept from the model
seas_model_no_intercept <- lm(data.notrend ~ months - 1)

# Print coefficients of the model without intercept
print(coefficients(seas_model_no_intercept))
##    months1    months2    months3    months4    months5    months6    months7

  for (j in 1: norder) {
    modij <- arima(residuals, order = c(p[i],0,q[j]), method='ML')
    aic[i,j] <- modij$aic-2*(p[i]+q[j]+1)+2*(p[i]+q[j]+1)*n/(n-p[i]-q[j]-2)
  }
}

# Function to perform Augmented Dickey-Fuller test manually
adf_test <- function(x, lag.max = NULL) {
  if (is.null(lag.max)) {
    lag.max <- floor(12*(length(x)/100)^0.25)
  }
  
  p_values <- numeric(lag.max)
  for (k in 1:lag.max) {
    reg <- lm(diff(x) ~ lag(diff(x), k = k))
    p_values[k] <- summary(reg)$coefficients[2, "Pr(>|t|)"]
  }
  
  adf_stat <- min(abs(qnorm(p_values)))
  p_value <- 1 - pnorm(adf_stat)
  
  cat("Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test\n")
  cat("ADF Statistic:", adf_stat, "\n")
  cat("p-value:", p_value, "\n")
  
  if (p_value < 0.05) {
    cat("Reject null hypothesis: The series is stationary\n")
  } else {
    cat("Fail to reject null hypothesis: The series is not stationary\n")
  }
  
  return(list(statistic = adf_stat, p.value = p_value))
}

# Check for homoscedasticity (Breusch-Pagan test)
# Calculate residuals
residuals <- data.notrend - fitted(seas.6)

# Fit a linear model to test for homoscedasticity
model <- lm(residuals^2 ~ fitted(seas.6))

# Extract residuals from the model
model_residuals <- residuals(model)

# Perform Breusch-Pagan test manually
n <- length(model_residuals)
x <- seq_len(n)

# Fit a linear model to the squared residuals
lm_squared_residuals <- lm(model_residuals^2 ~ x)

# Obtain the test statistic
bp_test_statistic <- summary(lm_squared_residuals)$fstatistic[1]

# Calculate the p-value
bp_test_p_value <- pf(bp_test_statistic, 1, n - 2, lower.tail = FALSE)

# Print the test results
cat("Breusch-Pagan Test Results:\n")
## Breusch-Pagan Test Results:
cat("Test Statistic:", bp_test_statistic, "\n")
## Test Statistic: 5.902871
cat("p-value:", bp_test_p_value, "\n")
